  "body": "Hello nomiclabs,\r\n\r\nI started with the migration from Buidler to Hardhat in one of my repositories. https://github.com/NRS-Soft/nuclearistrack on the \"hardhat-migration\" branch. with this commit https://github.com/NRS-Soft/nuclearistrack/commit/4bd9ada21f82e9de1dd25c6746e3c4117cc22cb3\r\n\r\nI followed your guide https://hardhat.org/guides/migrate-from-buidler.html\r\nBut once completed the guide I get the following error message on `npx hardhat compile` or `npx hardhat test` command:\r\n```\r\n[Error: EISDIR: illegal operation on a directory, read] {\r\n  errno: -21,\r\n  code: 'EISDIR',\r\n  syscall: 'read'\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs far as I know it has something to do with Node trying to read from a directory where it hasn't the permission.\r\nI tried to change the paths in the `hardhat.config.js` countless times but couldn't make it work..\r\n\r\nIf you have any clues or eventually already encountered this problem please let me know, with Buidler everything worked fine.\r\nI tried it with Node 10, 12 and even 14.\r\n\r\nIf you need any further information to reproduce the issue or eventually there is something big I'm missing.\r\n\r\nThank you very much!",
