    "body": "@alcuadrado thank you very much. Each time after running `npx hardhat clean` I'm able to run `npx hardhat compile` or `npx hardhat test` once and then I have to run `npx hardhat clean` again. It seems that somehow the files that get created give Node a hard time. I added an output of the `git diff` command after running `npx hardhat compile`\r\n\r\n```\r\n create mode 100644 cache/solidity-files-cache.json\r\n create mode 100644 src/contracts/artifacts/build-info/592798ec-4031-472d-bee9-fafa3eb91f8e.json\r\n create mode 100644 src/contracts/artifacts/src/contracts/NuclearPoE.sol/NuclearPoE.dbg.json\r\n create mode 100644 src/contracts/artifacts/src/contracts/NuclearPoE.sol/NuclearPoE.json\r\n create mode 100644 src/contracts/artifacts/src/contracts/Ownable.sol/Ownable.dbg.json\r\n create mode 100644 src/contracts/artifacts/src/contracts/Ownable.sol/Ownable.json\r\n create mode 100644 src/contracts/artifacts/src/contracts/Process.sol/Process.dbg.json\r\n create mode 100644 src/contracts/artifacts/src/contracts/Process.sol/Process.json\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs requested I link you to the `tree` output of the project, one is with the `npx hardhat clean` command and one after testing, and I added also a extract of the `git diff` command with the files that get created\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/sebastinez/ede132d24351fe15d4252f208a10e6f1\r\n\r\nEventually there is some problem with the way I structured my project, and the paths I used, I send you my `hardhat.config.js` file.\r\nhttps://github.com/NRS-Soft/nuclearistrack/blob/hardhat-migration/hardhat.config.js\r\n\r\nThank you very much!",
